# Vapi Webhook Handler Rules

## Incoming Request Shape

Every Vapi tool-call webhook delivers a POST body with this structure. Always validate with the zod schema from `src/webhooks/schemas.ts`:

```typescript
interface VapiToolCallRequest {
  message: {
    type: "tool-calls";
    call: Record<string, unknown>;
    toolWithToolCallList: Array<{
      name: string;
      toolCall: {
        id: string;
        parameters: Record<string, unknown>;
      };
    }>;
  };
}
```

## Required Response Shape

Every handler MUST return this exact structure via `c.json()`:

```typescript
interface VapiToolCallResponse {
  results: Array<{
    toolCallId: string;
    result?: string;
    error?: string;
  }>;
}
```

## Hard Rules

- Always return HTTP 200, even when reporting errors. Vapi ignores non-200 responses.
- `result` and `error` values must be flat, single-line strings. Never return objects, arrays, or multi-line strings.
- Match `toolCallId` from the request exactly — copy it, do not generate a new one.
- Validate every incoming payload with the zod schema before processing. Return a structured error result on validation failure.
- Handlers must complete within 5 seconds (Vapi timeout). Our internal target is < 300ms.
- Use Hono's `c.json()` to send responses. Do not construct raw `Response` objects.
- Never throw unhandled exceptions — catch all errors and return them as `{ error: "..." }` in the results array.
